FBIS3-60088 "jptdd003__l94053" JPRS-TDD-94-003-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 19 January 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL Four Detained After 1.5 Kg of Cocaine Seized at Tel Aviv Post Office TA1501073594 TA1501073594 Article Type:BFN [Editorial Report] Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew on 12 January carries a report by Buqi Na'e on page 11 which says that at the beginning of this week, "1.5 kg of cocaine, worth some 1 million shekels, was seized at a Tel Aviv post office. It was sent here from Belgium. Four people were arrested on suspicion of attempting to smuggle it to Israel." Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew on 9 January, in a page 5 report by ITIM, writes that a police search of a Tel Aviv apartment on 7 January revealed "over 4 kg of marijuana, as well as seeds, tobacco, and a marijuana plant." The two apartment owners were detained.
